Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
loadWorkspace(25.10)                                      loadWorkspace(25.10)

Name
       loadWorkspace - Loads the named workspace from the specified directory

Syntax
       loadWorkspace

       [-help]

       -name <workspaceName>

       [-dir <directory>]

       Loads  the  named  workspace  from the specified directory. A workspace
       contains customized main window settings including:

              * Size and placement of window

              * Specific orientation of toolbars

              * Docking status

              * Visibility settings

       You can use the loadWorkspace command at any stage in the  design  flow
       to  load  a previously saved workspace. However, if you want Innovus to
       load a specific workspace automatically on starting, you need to  first
       set that workspace as default using the setDefaultWorkspace command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each loadWorkspace parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man loadWorkspace

       -name <workspaceName>
              Specifies the name of the workspace to be loaded.

       -dir <directory>
              Specifies  the  directory  from  which  the  workspace  is to be
              loaded. The default search order to access directories for load-
              ing workspaces is as below:

              * Current working directory

              * User home directory

              The -dir parameter is useful if you  have  workspaces  with  the
              same  name  in  both the current working directory and your home
              directory. If you do not specify -dir, the  software  loads  the
              <workspaceName> workspace from the current working directory.

Example
       The  following example loads the MyWorkspace workspace from the current
       working directory.

       loadWorkspace -name MyWorkspace

